`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- The **vertex-based corner detection** is the key algorithm: iterating `(size+1)²` vertices and checking how many walls radiate outward maps cleanly to piece types — 2-perpendicular → round corner, 3+ → triangle junction. This is the geometrically correct complement to the cell-wall iteration in Phase 1
- **Extending the `HedgePiece` interface** with `pieceType/sizeClass/junction` was the right architectural move — it made `mazeGenerator.ts`'s mapping trivial and removed the fragile `extractSizeClass` string parser that only handled basic-type paths
